50 years married today.  You are a testimony to honor, love and commitment and I thank God every day that he made you my parents.  I love you ❤️Happy anniversary!
Strong, humble, kind, tough but loving, and would give anyone the shirt off his back.  Now that’s a dad.  And that’s my dad.  Happy Father’s Day!  I love you 💙

Dear Angel….
Oh all the beautiful memories we made and all the places we’ve been together.  You went from being a timid rescue to being a champion runner, fence jumper and face licker.  You were a strong protector and a playful and loyal best friend.  You were incredibly intuitive and smart and listened so well, always wanting to be the best girl, teaching your brother Earl how to be a good pup.  You followed me everywhere and I had no fear when you were by my side.  There was none more loyal than you and as cliche as it sounds, we didn’t rescue you, you rescued us. You lived up to your name.  I already miss you terribly and my heart is breaking, but I know that you are eating all the treats, jumping high, greeting everyone proudly with a bone in your mouth and running free with the angel pups.  Goodbye my sweet girl.  I love you.  I’ll see you later…somewhere over the rainbow 💙
